                <h1>Expert Guide: Prepping Walls for Peel and Stick Wallpaper</h1>
                <p>To prep walls for peel and stick wallpaper, ensure the surface is clean, smooth, and dry. Start by washing the walls with a mild detergent to remove dust and grease. Fill any holes or imperfections and sand them down. Finally, apply a primer if needed for better adhesion, allowing it to dry fully before installing the wallpaper.</p>
